cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.SOC, cs.HC 

This paper discusses the issue of addressing "bad actors" online, which involves aspects of cybersecurity (cs.CR), social media (cs.SOC), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The focus on defining acceptable and unacceptable behaviors and considering social structures suggests a potential fit with the categories of cyberculture (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
